						<summary>

						<p>Slab built into the wall of the Īśvara temple.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">13th century A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>It states that Sōmaya Son-in-law [aḷiya] of <hi rend="italic">mahāsāmanta</hi> Dāsaṇna and Māchi <hi rend="italic">gavuṇḍa</hi> together made a gift of six <hi rend="italic">mattar</hi> of land and a garden to the god Mahadēva of Gaṅga riṅguṇige.</p>						

						<p>It is in characters of the 13th century A.D. </p>						

						</summary>
